  "description": [
    "I The CoOperative Trades and Labor Council met Tuesday night in the new labor temple on South Second street The meeting was presided over by President Stanley Ogg and did not ad journ until about 11 oclock Forty delegates were present The credentials of Edward Bacon of the Teamsters Union C S Jame son of the Pattern Makers Union Jack Scheaf John Janser and Clarcnce Hazelett of Theatrical Stage Em ploye Union L A Brown of Paint ers and Paper Hangers Union and John G Curtis of Stationary Engin eers Union were read received and delegates installed The minutes of the previous meet ing were read and approved A tele gram was read from John Fitzpatrick chairman of the labor bureau on Irish independence regarding protest against the deportation of Lord Mayor Donal OCalahan which would mean his death was received Union labor temple committee of New Orleans La in a communication requested that the council purchase a brick for the benefit of their new tem Offering yott a saving of 11 1111 ltKM Prices still further reduced in order to clear our stocks of SUITS COATS DRESSES SKIRTS SWEATERS ple The letter was received because the delegates were of"
